The fundamental rights under Part III of the Constitution of India are guaranteed by various articles. Specifically, Article 19 (Part III — FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS) protects certain rights regarding freedom of speech, etc., which includes the right to:

(a) freedom of speech and expression;
(b) assemble peaceably and without arms;
(c) form associations or unions or co-operative societies;
(d) move freely throughout the territory of India;
(e) reside and settle in any part of the territory of India;
